details.description: Welcome to Coffee Republic in Matthews, NC—your destination for top-tier coffee that fuels your hustle! Since 2019, we've passionately served expertly roasted beans and handcrafted beverages made with love. Our cozy shop is the perfect spot for your daily java fix. Join us for an unmatched coffee experience and the finest brews.

raw_data.typical_time_spent: People typically spend up to 1.5 hours here

reviews_data.review_text: Very tasty coffee and a very chill place to hang out with friends

Liam was so fun had an amazing attitude that woke me up more than the coffee he served me.
I got the salted caramel latte and it was the best tasting coffee I have had in a while I definitely found my forever coffee home ❤️
It was my first time at this coffee shop and Molly was so kind & helpful in describing the menu! I ended up getting the Morning Buzz and it was exactly what I was looking for. Definitely coming back!
I go here literally every day to do work/chill, and I am never disappointed. Shout-out the entire team for making amazing Chai Latte's, especially Molly.
Molly was so sweet and helpful! Great customer service and great coffee!
Molly is a ray of sunshine! Brought great vibes and yummy food to my day ☀️ Definitely recommend this place as a staple!
I just started going to coffee republic and I've been getting the salty dog and its so good and its always nice talking to Molly one of my favorite coffee shops to visit bc of her!

I’ve visited numerous coffee shops in the area, but Republic Coffee stands out as the best. While I don’t require a wider variety of bakery items, the coffee quality compels me to make a special effort to visit at least once a week. The journey is worth it for the exceptional taste of their coffee.
I have been coming here all summer and the baristas have been awesome! Molly especially has been incredible! Would highly recommend!
Consistently excellent coffee and service. Easily the best in Matthews. The baristas are all wonderful too- especially Molly!

The team at Coffee Republic is the best - they hook it up every morning! Special shoutout to Molly who was on top of it this morning with a busy cafe - stellar job

Best latte's in town and worth a try if you're in the area.

Tried the Nutty Truffle Latte. It’s pretty freaking good! One of the first coffees in a LOOONG time that I truly enjoyed.

Highly recommend Coffee Republic to all coffee drinkers, amateur or professional. Their menu options are creative, customizable, and never fail to impress!

today i came in and i ordered the calm bean and molly made it and it was sooooo good she's so sweet and i will be returning one of the best coffee shops i've been too in awhile honestly and im a barista too so it says a lot ..... cute names too :)

The guy behind the counter just stared at me when I walked up. No greeting, just blank stare and then shrugged without saying anything until I ordered.

Ordered a chocolate croissant that was barely cooked. Very floppy and doughy with no crisp to it. Ordered a latte. It was just ok.

If the food/coffee made up for the service I would have moved on like it was a basic, pretentious coffee bar but the whole experience was bad. First time going there and I won’t go back.
It's a great coffee shop! Drinks were very good. Customer service is the best!

I really like this place and go there almost every Sunday. They have a great selection of coffee and snacks.
One thing every Coffee Republic seems to suffer from is extremely slow service. The place is empty and it still takes 10 min+ to get an espresso.
Bring some time.
Molly and rest of the staff is great, the food and drinks hit the spot. Good spot to go with friends!
Molly was great! Will be coming back soon
My coffee was delicious, and Molly was so adorable ! Thanks a lot, I’ll definitely come back 🫶🏻
Love this place, it's a vibe.  Great staff, glad to see Molly and the others daily.  Coffee A+

Decided to try Coffee Republic for some tea or coffee. I wasn't in the mood for coffee, so I ordered a London Fog which is Earl Grey tea, steamed milk, and vanilla syrup. It was ok. The Dirty Chai was much better. It's black tea, steamed milk, spices plus an espresso shot. This drink will wake you up! Both drinks cost $13.89, which isn't bad. Stop in and support your local coffee shop.
Every coffee I have had there has been delicious and the employees are so friendly! Love this new coffee shop.

So I stopped by just to grab a quick drink and snack, and let me say—I was pleasantly surprised. I got the strawberry refresher and a chocolate croissant, and both were absolutely DELICIOUS. The refresher was perfectly cold, not watered down like some places, and actually tasted like strawberries (imagine that!). The croissant? Warm, flaky, and honestly way better than what I’ve gotten at big-name coffee shops. Molly was super sweet and clearly knows what she’s doing. I’m picky, and this was a 10/10.
I always have great coffee and food from there. The staff is amazing and Molly always helps me.

I love this place! The atmosphere is so welcoming, and Molly was super sweet and helpful with my indecisiveness. Super glad I listened to her advice and tried the Snickerdoole Latte, as it will now be my current obsession!
Molly was fantastic—friendly, attentive, and made a great drink recommendation based on my coffee likes. She knows what she’s doing! I’ll definitely be coming back!

Came in a few days ago and ordered the sugar daddy latte. I had the pleasure of getting my latte made by Molly B. Molly was such a sweet interesting girl. As she made my order she genuinely tried to connect with me. We both related on the fact we both work at a coffee shop and talked about the pros and cons of working as a barista. Would recommend this location and Molly to any of my friends and family!
Love this coffee shop!  Best coffee and iced drinks around!  Fast, Friendly and knowledgeable service by Molly!  This will become my favorite spot!  Highly recommend!

I usually order the *Calm Bean* — it's my go-to drink and a signature menu item you can only find at Coffee Republic. Smooth, unique, and truly calming — just like the name!

What makes my experience even better is Molly. She is absolutely wonderful — always warm, attentive, and remembers my order with a smile. Molly’s kindness and consistent service keep me coming back. She truly represents the heart of the café!

The entire team is friendly, Molly stands out in the best way. Thank you, Molly, and thank you Coffee Republic for such a cozy and welcoming space!

Enticed by the generous, free 12 oz coffee with email sign-up, I was delighted by not only that great dark roast, but super pleased by the friendly, welcoming, and knowledgeable staff and the comfortable, cool, and eclectic atmosphere: one of my best coffee shop experiences in a while! (Oh right, and the French toast muffin was bomb, too :)

Passes the vibe check!  This place has great coffee, food, diverse music, plenty of chairs for customers and wifi.  Spent a few hours here while waiting for my dog to have a procedure done.  Worked during that time.  Definitely recommended!
The coffee shop is cute, but it smells like old cleaner in there. I got the breakfast burrito and it was nothing special - just came frozen and they heated it up. Coffee was ok.
Best coffee in the area

I somehow has been sleeping on coffee Republic Forks quiet sometime...... today I went in and Jonah and Liam made me an iced Irish Cream macchiato. They were friendly, kind, and courteous , which was a big deal to me because hospitality is everything. My drink turned out to be absolutely amazing! I will definitely be back soon, you guys take care and God bless
Nothing special...the people are nice.
Great coffee !

I really like this place.  One example,  I bought a bag of coffee beans but then remembered my machine only does ground.  The staff offered to ground them for me.  Also, the strawberry matcha is best that I had from this place.  Stellar service, great matcha, and the place has a cool vibe to it.
Love Coffee Republic! They renovated beautifully and the lattes are fabulous!
5 stars all around !! Love this place! Friendly baristas love the lattes and the silly names ! Ellie is the sweetest kindest best barista ever I love her
Great Coffee

Coffee is great and they have such fun lattes! I also loveee their peanut butter protein bites, so good! Everyone I have met has been so kind and nice, especially the lead manager. He is always there when I go in and he always makes sure I love what I have gotten! Highly recommend!

Nothing special. Low selection of pastries (it was still early in the morning) and it took a while to get out coffee drinks. It's an inviting place, but lacks enough seating. Maybe this is more of a to-go place for coffee!? It was a big rave over an average place. Drive a half hour to try this place. I would come again only if in the area.

Excellent location
Great coffee
Love the seating layout

That French toast muffin is crazy good!! I also really loved my latte as well. Isaiah was very kind and provided great service. When my food was ready, he brought it over to me with some napkins which was very thoughtful. I’ll definitely be back again soon!! Cool atmosphere and peaceful music.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Thank you so much for your kind words, Chloe! We're happy to hear that you loved the French toast muffin and your latte—great choices! Isaiah will be delighted to know he made your visit even more enjoyable. 

We can’t wait to welcome you back for another relaxing coffee break. See you soon at Coffee Republic in Matthews!

reviews_data.review_text: Their coffee is incredibly overpriced for the taste. 🤷‍♀️ Been 3 times and each time it's tasted burnt or overbrewed. Not my favorite to pay $8+ for a coffee for it to be disgusting. And the last time I went, the gentleman working there acted like my 5 year old ordering for herself was an inconvenience. I won't be going back for multiple reasons.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Kaitlin,

We’re really sorry to hear about your experience at Coffee Republic. We strive to provide high-quality coffee and excellent service, so it’s disappointing to know we missed the mark during your visits. Your feedback about the taste and pricing is valuable, and we’ll certainly take it into account to improve.

We also want every customer—especially our youngest guests—to feel welcome, and we regret that this wasn’t the case. If you’d be open to discussing this further, please reach out to us at daniel@coffeerepub.com. We’d love the opportunity to make things right.

If you’re ever in Matthews again, we’d love for you to give us another try. We’re always working to enhance our coffee and customer experience!

Warm regards,
Daniel Coco
Charlotte Area Market Manager
Coffee Republic

reviews_data.review_text: Amazing service and excellent coffee
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much, Nichole! We're thrilled to hear that you enjoyed our service and coffee. Your kind words mean the world to us! Next time you're in Matthews, we’d love to see you at Coffee Republic—stop by for another great cup of coffee. Hope to serve you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Great coffee place.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you, Wes! We’re so glad you enjoyed our place. We appreciate your support and hope to see you again soon at Coffee Republic in Matthews! Cheers!

reviews_data.review_text: Amazing staff ,great coffee and just a walk away from the thrift all a girl could ever ask for 💚
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Thank you, Ana! We’re so glad you enjoyed our coffee and service. It’s always a pleasure to provide a great experience for our customers. 

Next time you're in the area, stop by Coffee Republic for another delicious cup—we’d love to see you again!

reviews_data.review_text: They forgot to brew my coffee being busy chatting with each other other. Tables are dirty, macaroon was served in the cup, what? And yes, coffee is nasty and serving in the paper cup for dine in.
reviews_data.owner_answer:

Daniel Coco
Charlotte Area Market Manager
Daniel@coffeerepub.com

reviews_data.review_text: Good coffee and cozy atmosphere.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you, Serge! We're so glad you enjoyed the coffee and cozy atmosphere. Coffee Republic in Matthews is all about great brews and a welcoming space to relax. We’d love to see you again soon—stop by for another cup and try one of our delicious pastries! See you!

reviews_data.review_text: The coffee was delicious and so were the pastries and you get all that with friendly service which is hard to come by these days.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for you awesome feedback Tyesha! We look forward to serving you again soon.

reviews_data.review_text:
I first tried this place when they just opened and got a latte. It was terrible. I figured they were still getting the hang of things, so I gave it another shot a couple of weeks later. Nope.. still bad.
Today I decided to try one last time instead of going to starbucks, thinking Third time’s a charm. But it was just as bad as the first two times. I honestly don’t understand where all these amazing reviews are coming from. I’m definitely disappointed and won’t be coming back.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Dear Elana,

Thank you for taking the time to share your feedback with us. I’m deeply sorry to hear that your experiences with us haven’t met your expectations, despite giving us multiple chances to improve. Your disappointment is understandable, and we truly regret that we’ve let you down.

At Coffee Republic, we strive to deliver exceptional products and experiences for every guest, and it’s clear that we missed the mark in your case. I sincerely appreciate your honesty—it helps us identify areas where we need to grow.

We’re committed to learning from this and improving, and I would love the opportunity to make things right. I’d be happy to offer you a full refund or provide a credit for you to use if you decide to give us another chance in the future. Please let us know what feels best for you—we’re willing to do whatever it takes to make this right.

Your feedback motivates us to work diligently on enhancing our products and guest experience. I hope you might consider giving us another shot down the road, as we would love the chance to change your opinion.

Thank you again for sharing your thoughts and for giving us multiple opportunities. We truly value your input and your time.

Warm regards,
Daniel Coco
Charlotte Area Market Manager
Daniel@coffeerepub.com

reviews_data.review_text: Their drip coffee is good. Appears to be popular with the locals.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Thank you, Sri, for your kind words! We're glad you enjoyed our drip coffee. It’s always wonderful to see locals and new visitors alike enjoying a great cup of coffee at Coffee Republic. 

Next time you stop by, we’d love for you to try one of our specialty drinks or pastries! Hope to see you again soon in Matthews!

reviews_data.review_text: This café is a breath of fresh air! Their attention to sustainability and community involvement is inspiring. The coffee is amazing, and the relaxed vibe makes it a great escape from the daily grind
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Thank you, Robert! We're so glad you enjoyed our café and appreciated our commitment to sustainability and community. It means a lot to us! We love creating a welcoming space where you can relax and enjoy amazing coffee. 

Next time you're in the area, we’d love for you to stop by Coffee Republic in Matthews and experience another great cup. See you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Coffee Republic is a must-visit! Their seasonal drinks are always creative and delicious. Plus, the cozy atmosphere and friendly baristas make it feel like home. I’ve never had a bad experience here
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Thank you, Joshua! We truly appreciate your kind words and are so glad you enjoy our seasonal drinks and welcoming atmosphere. Our team loves crafting unique flavors and making Coffee Republic a place where everyone feels at home. 

We look forward to serving you again soon—stop by and try our latest seasonal creation! See you!

reviews_data.review_text: Highly recommended! Overall Service and prices are great. The employees were friendly. When you go, try their dirty chai tea and Chile verde breakfast burrito!

I'm so glad I stumbled upon this place! The attention to detail in every cup of coffee is impressive. The café's interior is inviting, with comfortable spaces to relax or catch up with friends. A must-visit for coffee lovers

Hands down the best coffee shop in Matthews! The vibe is welcoming, the staff is knowledgeable, and the coffee is consistently excellent. Their pastries are delicious too — perfect for pairing with a freshly brewed cappuccino

Coffee Republic never disappoints! Whether you’re in the mood for a classic espresso or a creative seasonal drink, they’ve got it covered. The cozy atmosphere makes it a wonderful escape from the hustle and bustle

The perfect blend of community and coffee! The baristas here are skilled and passionate, which shows in the quality of every drink. The Nutty Truffle is my favorite — rich, creamy, and just the right amount of sweetness
Wonderful coffee, wonderful service!
Highly recommended! 💯🔥🫡
Some of the best customer service I've experienced. This place is a must go!!!
This spot is top notch!  It’s my go-to when traveling for work, and I stop by every time.  Staff is super friendly and coffee is AMAZING.  Highly recommend!
Amazing service, food and the environment is great.
Great!
Great experience! Friendly staff and worth the money .

Been here 4 times now. Started with a standard Latte which was weak, tried again and it was the same. Decided to give them a third chance and went to drip coffee. Was pretty much water and couldn't add any cream or it would be over creamed. Tried one more time and I'm throwing in the towel. On my 3rd and 4th visits there was a very nice batista too bad it didn't match coffee quality.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Dear Mark,

First of all, thank you so much for taking the time to share your feedback. We truly value and appreciate every review, as it helps us learn and grow. I’m really sorry to hear that your experiences with us haven’t met your expectations—particularly after multiple visits.

It’s clear that we’ve missed the mark with our coffee quality, and I apologize for any disappointment caused. We absolutely understand how frustrating it can be when a product doesn’t live up to the standards you expect, especially when you've made the effort to give us several chances.

We’re constantly working to improve both our products and the overall guest experience, and your feedback will certainly help guide our efforts. To make this right, we’d love to offer you a refund for your most recent purchase or provide you with a store credit for any future visit. Whatever you feel is best, we’re happy to accommodate.

Additionally, I’d be grateful for the chance to personally ensure your next experience with us exceeds expectations. We’re always striving to perfect our craft, and we’d love to have you back to see the improvements we’re making.

Thank you again for your honesty and for giving us the opportunity to address this. We truly hope we can earn your trust again in the future.

Warmly,
Daniel Coco
Charlotte Area Market Manager
Coffee Republic

reviews_data.review_text: Great coffee, great atmosphere, and even better service! I love starting my mornings here. The cozy decor and ample seating make it a wonderful spot for early morning work sessions or just enjoying a peaceful cup of coffee.

Y’all, I have to say it is very often that I give a place one star. I would have gone back to have them make this right… But I was already halfway down the road… This was the worst coffee I have ever had in my life, and I don’t even consider myself a coffee snob.

I thought that I would check them out, first timer here. I had cold brew with oat milk… It tasted disgusting… I actually have to admit that I would’ve rather have just gone to the big box store coffee shop that’s on every corner, but I love to support local.  So disappointing, unfortunately
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Jenna!

Thank you so much for taking the time to share your experience with us. I’m truly sorry to hear that your cold brew with oat milk didn’t meet your expectations. We absolutely understand how disappointing it can be when a first visit doesn’t go as hoped, and we sincerely apologize for the negative experience.

We’re grateful for your support of local businesses, and we never want to let our guests down. Please know that we’re actively working to improve our products and guest experiences, and your feedback is incredibly valuable to us in that process.

If you’re open to it, we’d love the opportunity to make things right. We can offer a refund or provide a credit for your next visit—whatever would best suit you. Please don’t hesitate to let us know what would help resolve the situation for you.

Again, we truly appreciate your feedback and the time you took to share it with us. We hope to have the chance to serve you better in the future.

Warm regards,
Daniel Coco
Charlotte Area Market Manager

reviews_data.review_text: I order coffee here through the app nearly every day. 90% of the time my coffee is made until I arrive and often times after customers who arrive after me. A newer hire doesn't greet you and does not speak up when conversing with you. They also struggled getting another customers order ahead of time and resulted in waiting an additional 15-20 minutes. Keep in mind I order through the app 15-20, sometimes 30 minutes in advance. I sent the feedback through their site before, there was no change, have now left a review. Going to seek somewhere else to get my coffee.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Ben!

First, I want to thank you for sharing such detailed feedback. I can only imagine how frustrating it must be to look forward to your coffee and then have your experience fall short of expectations—especially when you’ve taken the time to pre-order, sometimes well in advance. It’s clear that we missed the mark, and for that, I’m truly sorry.

We absolutely understand how important consistency is, particularly when you’ve come to rely on us for your daily coffee fix. To hear that you’ve had multiple experiences where your order was delayed, or you were made to feel unimportant, is not acceptable, and we will absolutely be addressing this with our team to ensure it doesn’t continue.

We’re always working to improve both our products and our customer service, and your review is a crucial part of that process. I’m grateful for your patience, and I sincerely apologize for any inconvenience this caused. I’d love the opportunity to make this right for you. Whether that means a refund for your last purchase or a credit towards a future visit, I’m happy to do whatever you feel would best address your experience.

I truly hope you’ll give us another chance. If there’s anything specific we can do to improve your visits moving forward, please don’t hesitate to reach out directly. We value your business and would love to welcome you back when you’re ready.

Thank you again for taking the time to share your thoughts. Your feedback makes us better, and we’re committed to showing you a much better experience next time.

Best,
Daniel Coco
Charlotte Area Market Manager
Coffee Republic

reviews_data.review_text: Absolutely love this place! The coffee is rich and flavorful, with a perfect balance of strength and smoothness. The atmosphere is cozy, making it an ideal spot to relax or get some work done. Highly recommend their lattes — always brewed to perfection!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for your 5 star review Joseph! We love to hear positive feedback about our organic Disco coffee and stellar customer service. We look forward to serving you again soon.

reviews_data.review_text: I was optimistic about this place but after trying it, am so disappointed that it has new ownership and is nothing like the previous shop! The interior is modern, but lacks the cozy vibe that Dilworth had. The most upsetting part was the sticker shock of ordering a tiny piece of quiche only to realize it was almost $9– tasted good but that price is insane!! Before leaving a review I wanted to also try coffee— so I ordered a latte, and again faced the insanity of overcharging— oat milk costs an additional $1.35– $8 for a latte with no flavoring/syrup. The coffee wasn’t bad but wasn’t great by any means— espresso tasted burnt. The barista was nice but there’s obviously poor management going on as it’s Veterans Day and witnessed a vet come in for a free drip coffee (as posted on Instagram) and was told that the store wasn’t offering it. He left visibly upset. Certainly will not be returning and will be continuing to grieve the loss of Dilworth coffee!!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Alyssa, we always appreciate feedback so we can continue to grow and offer the best service to our guests. The ownership of Coffee Republic has never changed, we’re a family owned coffee shop from the Charlotte area. We take pride in our coffee as it is locally roasted and organically certified. We’re thrilled you liked the quiche and would love to offer you a fresh latte as our staff is constantly learning and improving.

reviews_data.review_text: Ana was amazing when my friend and I came late, she was so nice and attentive and made amazing coffee! You guys should check them out!

I went to Coffee Republic for the first time with a friend and now I am hooked. I went back within 2 days. The coffee is smooth, bold and a little nutty in flavor. Best cup of coffee I have had in years! I will not go back to Starbucks as long as I am close to a Coffee Republic.  The want to try the Ballantyne location next, it appears larger and more space and I need to try a pastry too.
Stopped by for my first time this week!  Had a delicious vegan brownie bar and an iced vanilla latte with soy milk!  Both were so good!  So glad to have them here!

Coffee Republic Georgetown is my go-to café for a reason! The coffee is expertly crafted, with each cup showcasing rich flavors that are hard to find elsewhere. The cozy atmosphere invites you to linger a little longer, whether you’re working or catching up with friends. The staff always makes you feel at home
Love the coffee but unfortunately will not visit this location again. One employee during morning rush is complete insanity Paid and couldn’t wait any longer took and took a raincheck.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for your feedback - we hope to have you back for a quicker and better experience.

reviews_data.review_text: Coffee Republic in Matthews is a gem. The coffee is always delicious, and the staff is incredibly welcoming. A great place to stop by for a high-quality coffee experience
reviews_data.owner_answer: We appreciate you!

reviews_data.review_text: I’ve given this place so many chances and they’re just so unprofessional with the absolute worse customer service. There’s no sense of urgency no matter how many people are in line and I will never return. The coffee isn’t good enough to ruin my day.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Jenna!

First, thank you for sharing your feedback with us. I’m truly sorry to hear about your repeated negative experiences and the frustration you’ve encountered. We never want to be the source of your dissatisfaction, and it’s clear we missed the mark with both the service and the overall experience you had with us. I completely understand why you’re upset, and I genuinely appreciate the time you took to express your concerns.

We pride ourselves on offering not just great coffee but also great service, and it’s disheartening to hear that we haven’t been able to meet those expectations during your visits. Your comments about the lack of urgency and professionalism are absolutely something we’ll be taking to heart as we work on improving our processes and training.

I’d like to make this right for you, and I’m more than happy to offer a refund on your recent purchase or provide a credit for a future visit—whichever you feel would be best. Our goal is to leave our customers satisfied, and I’d love the opportunity to show you that we can do better.

Again, I’m truly sorry that your experience hasn’t been what it should have been, and I hope you’ll consider giving us another chance to demonstrate the improvements we’re working hard to implement.

Thank you for your honesty and for the chance to improve. If there’s anything specific you’d like to discuss or any way we can do better, please don’t hesitate to reach out directly.

Best,
Daniel Coco
Charlotte Area Market Manager
Coffee Republic

reviews_data.review_text:
Pleasant service. Hot latte had nice foam but coffee flavor was weak for my taste. Bacon, egg and cheese burrito was on some kind of flakey wrap with a crust rather than a tortilla and the contents were
tasteless.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Not the experience we want you to have. We’d like to invite you back in for an improved experience- please email us at info@coffeerepub.com

reviews_data.review_text: Great experience. They had a no-show, so the VP and Director were running the place this morning. Very knowledgeable and provided great conversation.

This is nothing compared to the coffee shop here before, Dilworth Coffee. Dilworth Coffee had amazing coffee, quality service, and a community atmosphere. My wife and I came here every Saturday and always met someone new and had the best experience. This new coffee shop is disappointing and can’t live up to its predecessor.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We are constantly working to improve and would love to invite you back in for a better experience. Please send us an email info@coffeerepub.com

reviews_data.review_text: Service was terrible. Person taking my order had no customer service skills and was rude. Coffee was bad. Waste of 8$. People were kind at Dilworth Coffee and atmosphere was better. Won’t be returning.

This was my first time at any Coffee Republic. They made a significant improvement to the interior. This space used to be Dilworth Coffee. It feels more open now. The French toast muffin was delicious! The iced caramel latte was pretty good. My bar on coffee/caramel lattes will always be Not Just Coffee. The service was excellent when I was there. They only had one barista working, and it was pretty busy. She did a fantastic job managing all of the customers. They probably need two baristas on staff for the morning. Overall, Coffee Republic is an improvement over Dillworth Coffee, and I will be back!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much for your feedback! We will continue to strive to offer great service ☕️

reviews_data.review_text: It took 30 minutes for 2 pour overs, the water wasn't hot..also weird, hipster pictures. Strange atmosphere that seems meant for uptown.
Good coffee but slow service(of course one person can’t make so many orders at the same time so it makes sense).
I LOVE this place and ESPECIALLY enjoyed Trevor, my new favorite barista! He took his time allowing me to explore and helped me find the coffee of my dreams!

This is certainly not the coffee, service or atmosphere Im looking for especially first thing in the morning.  Nothing but a corporation vibe with the electronic boards, horrible seating and bad customer service.  Plus, don't get me started on the "fresh" pastries and the horrible prices.  If you want a nice neighborhood coffee house you will need to look elsewhere.
reviews_data.owner_answer: As a family owned business, we strive to offer the best service. We hope you’ll be back and give us another chance.

reviews_data.review_text: The coffee has been perfect every time! Hands down my favorite local coffee spot!

While I like the coffee shop itself the baristas were arguing and criticizing each other during my 15 minutes in the shop. Also one of the baristas had a crop top on. While this in a general setting doesn't bother me, when handling food as they do and her stomach touching the counter I was very close to leaving altogether. I have had an iced drink there a few times now and am just not impressed. Will not be returning

reviews_data.review_text: Great experience. They had a no-show, so the VP and Director were running the place this morning. Very knowledgeable and provided great conversation.

This is nothing compared to the coffee shop here before, Dilworth Coffee. Dilworth Coffee had amazing coffee, quality service, and a community atmosphere. My wife and I came here every Saturday and always met someone new and had the best experience. This new coffee shop is disappointing and can’t live up to its predecessor.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We are constantly working to improve and would love to invite you back in for a better experience. Please send us an email info@coffeerepub.com

reviews_data.review_text: Service was terrible. Person taking my order had no customer service skills and was rude. Coffee was bad. Waste of 8$. People were kind at Dilworth Coffee and atmosphere was better. Won’t be returning.

This was my first time at any Coffee Republic. They made a significant improvement to the interior. This space used to be Dilworth Coffee. It feels more open now. The French toast muffin was delicious! The iced caramel latte was pretty good. My bar on coffee/caramel lattes will always be Not Just Coffee. The service was excellent when I was there. They only had one barista working, and it was pretty busy. She did a fantastic job managing all of the customers. They probably need two baristas on staff for the morning. Overall, Coffee Republic is an improvement over Dillworth Coffee, and I will be back!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much for your feedback! We will continue to strive to offer great service ☕️

reviews_data.review_text: It took 30 minutes for 2 pour overs, the water wasn't hot..also weird, hipster pictures. Strange atmosphere that seems meant for uptown.
Good coffee but slow service(of course one person can’t make so many orders at the same time so it makes sense).
I LOVE this place and ESPECIALLY enjoyed Trevor, my new favorite barista! He took his time allowing me to explore and helped me find the coffee of my dreams!

This is certainly not the coffee, service or atmosphere Im looking for especially first thing in the morning.  Nothing but a corporation vibe with the electronic boards, horrible seating and bad customer service.  Plus, don't get me started on the "fresh" pastries and the horrible prices.  If you want a nice neighborhood coffee house you will need to look elsewhere.
reviews_data.owner_answer: As a family owned business, we strive to offer the best service. We hope you’ll be back and give us another chance.

reviews_data.review_text: The coffee has been perfect every time! Hands down my favorite local coffee spot!

While I like the coffee shop itself the baristas were arguing and criticizing each other during my 15 minutes in the shop. Also one of the baristas had a crop top on. While this in a general setting doesn't bother me, when handling food as they do and her stomach touching the counter I was very close to leaving altogether. I have had an iced drink there a few times now and am just not impressed. Will not be returning
Fantastic experience at Coffee Republic! The coffee is always fresh and flavorful, and the cozy setting makes it a great place to relax or work.
If you’re looking for high-quality coffee and a friendly atmosphere, Coffee Republic is the place to be. Their attention to detail in every cup makes it a standout spot

Coffee Republic in Matthews is a delight! The coffee is outstanding, and the environment is so welcoming. Perfect for a relaxing break or a productive work session. Highly recommend their specialty drinks
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much!

reviews_data.review_text: Exceptional coffee and a warm, inviting atmosphere at Coffee Republic. The baristas are skilled, and the quality of the drinks is always consistent. A must-visit for any coffee lover
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you!!

reviews_data.review_text: coffee was decent but desperately needs a new owner. had only one employee who had no clue what they were doing and clearly needed help. very unprofessional. obnoxious music playing and just not great atmosphere. so sad they replaced dilworth.

Spectacular coffee!
I got my usual latte and it was robust, bold and flavorful! I loved it!
I  was there in the afternoon, so their pastry selections were depleted, but I’d like to return and try a few of them!

The decor and feel is homey and unique.
There’s quite a bit of bar style seating and a few tables- inside and out.

If you like good coffee- this is the place for you!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much!

reviews_data.review_text: Great coffee shop!  The variety of products was amazing to see.  Good selection of breakfast treats and sweet treats.  Would highly recommend.
everything was great!! The whole experience was amazing
Good vibes and great coffee !
the best coffee shop ever!!
Best Coffee I've ever had, so glad they're in the neighborhood!
Their coffee is meh, pretty generically bland.  Not as good as Dilworth Coffee.

Coffee tastes great but the service was really BAD.  The cashier seemed rude and did not ask which option of coffee I wanted. Really?  Also, the two co-workers argued over the dates of the food instead of working on our orders.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We appreciate your feedback and are making improvements to offer better service.

reviews_data.review_text: Nice employees.  Got an iced Calm Bean latte, with oat milk, vanilla, lavender.  It was just right for me.  Not too sweet, could taste the flavors nicely. Good coffee flavor too.
Such a cute shop!! All the barista are super friendly and awesome to chat with! 10/10 highly recommend the Salty Dog latte and those strawberry croissants 🤤💛✨
